    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1410"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1410">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/289.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Willard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Please inform Foreign Office that we are in constant touch with Spanish
                    Ambassador and are assisting him in every way. Evidently many false reports are
                    being circulated in Spain. We would hear immediately if any violence was being
                    done or threatened to Spaniards in Mexico. Villa expelled Spaniards from Torreon
                    on the ground that they were actively participating with Federals but no
                    Spaniards were killed. We protested most earnestly against expulsion and have
                    cooperated with Spanish Ambassador in efforts to protect property. Say to
                    Foreign Office that the interests of foreigners have our constant care and
                    effort equally with American interests. Mediation is in progress and we are
                    hoping for satisfactory results.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
